					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Does it still happen when you render the background, but not sprites? My first guess is &quot;sprites.spr&quot; is not long enough, or has errors.<br /><br />My second guess is something similar with rogue.nam.<br /><br />The longshot:<br /><br />Behold, the way to draw all the colors on the screen at once: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Full_palette_demo">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Full_palette_demo</a><!-- m --><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Normally, the PPU displays the palette byte from $3F00 as the background color. When rendering is disabled and the PPU address is in the $3F00-$3FFF range, the PPU displays the palette byte at that address.</div><br />But the only way I can see that happening in the code you posted is if the sound engine wasn't set up to use unique RAM.<br /><br />Another potential issue is a negative scroll value for Y, but similarly I can't see anything that would cause that except RAM collisions here.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible">https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible</a><!-- m --></div>
