						<div class="postbody">If you would post an NES ROM as well, it would be very easy to tell what is causing any visual element that appears with a good debugging emulator (Mesen, FCEUX, Nintendulator, etc.)<br /><br />The assembly files are helpful as well for diagnosing a problem, but it's much easier to just check what the ROM is actually doing than either try to reason about what a bunch of code does.</div>

					
